The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and graph convolutional networks (GCNs) for computer vision tasks, indicating a likely fit with the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the training of deep GCNs, which suggests a potential fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of GCNs for protein function classification, indicating a possible fit with the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of residual/dense connections and dilated convolutions, which suggests a potential fit with the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
